## Quality Assurance Checklist

### Functionality Testing
- [ ] All buttons work correctly
- [ ] Forms submit properly
- [ ] Navigation functions
- [ ] Modals open/close
- [ ] Responsive behavior intact
- [ ] Animations/transitions smooth

### Accessibility Validation
- [ ] Screen reader compatibility
- [ ] Keyboard navigation works
- [ ] Focus indicators visible
- [ ] Color alone doesn't convey meaning
- [ ] Text meets contrast requirements
- [ ] Alt text for color-coded elements

### Visual Quality Check
- [ ] Colors appear consistent across browsers
- [ ] No color bleeding or artifacts
- [ ] Gradients render smoothly
- [ ] Print styles maintain readability
- [ ] High DPI displays look crisp

### Performance Impact
- [ ] No additional CSS bloat
- [ ] Images optimized for new color scheme
- [ ] No unnecessary re-renders
- [ ] Bundle size unchanged
- [ ] Load times maintained

## Post-Implementation Validation

### User Experience Testing
- [ ] Navigation feels intuitive
- [ ] CTAs are prominent and clear
- [ ] Content hierarchy is obvious
- [ ] Trust signals are enhanced
- [ ] Medical authority is conveyed

### Cross-Device Testing
- [ ] Desktop: All resolutions
- [ ] Tablet: Portrait and landscape
- [ ] Mobile: Various screen sizes
- [ ] Print: Readable in grayscale
- [ ] High contrast mode compatible

### Browser Compatibility
- [ ] Chrome/Chromium
- [ ] Firefox
- [ ] Safari
- [ ] Edge
- [ ] Mobile browsers

## Documentation Requirements

### Change Log
```markdown
## [Page Name] Color Enhancement
- **Changed**: [Specific elements updated]
- **Reason**: [SOI brand alignment/accessibility/UX]
- **Impact**: [User experience improvement]
- **Testing**: [Validation performed]
```

### Rollback Instructions
- [ ] Document original color values
- [ ] Note any structural changes made
- [ ] List dependencies affected
- [ ] Provide quick revert steps
- [ ] Test rollback procedure

